        "Story": "A classic Okheman delicacy — grilled dromas steak, best served on redsoil for the most authentic flavor. Much like cattle in many worlds, dromases used for meat are technically a different breed from those used for labor. This variety of dromas has tender and flavorful meat, but if not prepared properly, it's about as enjoyable as eating redsoil.<br><br><i>\"I heard that the Mountain Dwellers who revere Georios never eat dromas meat. Is that true?\"</i><br><i>\"Balderdash. Mountain Dweller, I am. When hungry, eat anything, especially if tastes good.\"</i>",
